			<description><![CDATA[<p>
Product Manager</p>
<p>
Are you passionate about creating world-class products? Interested in building and designing products used by millions of people? Do you like working in a fast-paced environment? Are you brilliant at what you do? Does everyone agree that your work is impeccable? Do you want to work in SoHo? Sound like you?</p>
<p>
Pixable is looking for a Product Manager to join its team. The person in this position will be responsible for developing the product specifications for customer engagement, retention and growth. This individual will interface with marketing, technical, and executive management to ensure strategic focus throughout planning and execution. The candidate must have the ability to understand and evaluate all aspects of product development and identify opportunities to improve the product.</p>
<p>
Responsibilities</p>
<p>
Lead the contribution to the product and feature design, including product specs and mock ups.<br />
Planning of implementation, i.e., identifying individual tasks, prioritizing them, assigning tasks to developers, and setting clear milestones with dates associated.<br />
Coordination of the execution until the product or feature is released.<br />
Research and market analysis (competitive benchmarking).<br />
Define and analyze metrics that inform the success of products.<br />
In this role, you will also be involved in the complete life cycle of each product and feature, getting involved in the marketing initiatives, usability studies, P&amp;Ls and analytics (A/B testing, tracking analytics, iterations, etc.).</p>
<p>
Qualifications</p>
<p>
2+ years of experience in a product management, marketing, or corporate strategy role within internet, tech, social media, game industry.<br />
Exceptional organizational and analytical skills.<br />
Data driven.<br />
Exceptional communication and presentation skills.<br />
Deep understanding of the mobile user experience.<br />
Eye for design and usability.<br />
Understanding of the technical architecture of complex and highly scalable web applications and/or media products.<br />
Experience designing simple and intuitive user interfaces - ability to create examples through wire frames and mock ups.<br />
Experience developing social products, technologies and platforms is strongly desired.<br />
Owner mindset: ability to take ownership of an issue and see it through resolution.<br />
Ability to be flexible on a day to day basis with task priority</p>
]]></description>
