QA and Test Engineer</p>
<p>
Pixable is looking for a Quality Assurance Engineer to join its team. This engineer will be the hub of all the engineering development process.</p>
<p>
Responsibilities</p>
<p>
Collaborate with development team in both agile and waterfall SDLC to achieve a complete understanding of company products and formulate testing strategies and solutions.<br />
Design, develop and deploy test procedures for our wide range of products.<br />
Working closely with the product and development teams to understand product requirements, architecture and technology.<br />
Triaging test execution results and validating against product requirements and with product teams. Filing bugs where appropriate.<br />
Define and analyze metrics that inform the success of products.<br />
Maintain and enhance existing automation test scripts used during Development and QA cycles.</p>
<p>
Qualifications<br />
2+ years of experience.<br />
Experience with Linux, PHP, MySQL, MongoDB, Apache, C.<br />
Experience with mobile QA environment and coding (Android SDK, xCode).<br />
Experience writing automation scripts.<br />
Experience with RESTful web services and cloud-based architectures.<br />
Basic expertise in object-oriented test design using open source tools (eg. Selenium, Chrome developer tools).<br />
Familiar with Social Network (Facebook, Twitter, etc) integrations.<br />
Detail-oriented.<br />
Communication skills (verbal and written).<br />
Experience working in a fast-paced environment that requires frequent shift in areas of focus.<br />
Ability to work independently and take initiative to solve problems and QA challenges.<br />
Experience with Agile and Scrum methodology.</p>
